            <h3 class="mt-4">Operational Benefits for E-commerce Platforms</h3>
            <p><strong>1. Enhanced Price Competitiveness</strong><br>
            GST deductions enable e-commerce platforms to offer products at significantly lower prices compared to traditional retail, especially when combined with online-exclusive discounts and deals.</p>
            
            <p><strong>2. Improved Supply Chain Efficiency</strong><br>
            Lower tax rates reduce the overall cost burden throughout the supply chain, enabling:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Better vendor negotiations</li>
                <li>Streamlined logistics costs</li>
                <li>Reduced working capital requirements</li>
                <li>Faster inventory turnover</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p><strong>3. Market Expansion Opportunities</strong><br>
            The price reduction resulting from GST deductions makes products accessible to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Price-sensitive consumer segments</li>
                <li>Tier-2 and Tier-3 city markets</li>
                <li>First-time online buyers</li>
                <li>Budget-conscious millennials and Gen-Z consumers</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p><strong>4. Category Expansion Potential</strong><br>
            Lower GST rates encourage e-commerce platforms to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Introduce new product categories</li>
                <li>Expand private label offerings</li>
                <li>Enter previously unviable market segments</li>
                <li>Develop subscription-based models</li>
            </ul>

